SURVIVAL STAGE DAY 1 | JULY 29

The 2025 PUBG MOBILE WORLD CUP at ESPORTS WORLD CUP enters a critical phase as the Survival Stage kicks off in Riyadh! The battle intensifies as teams fight for their last chance to reach the Grand Finals and claim their share of the massive $3,000,000 prize pool.

This stage is do-or-die. After the Group Stage, the top 8 teams already secured their Grand Finals slots—but for the remaining 16 teams, the Survival Stage is their only shot. Over the course of two days, these teams will clash head-to-head, with only 8 advancing to Grand Finals. The pressure is immense. The stakes? Everything.

The Survival Stage is where stories are rewritten and underdogs rise. With limited spots left, every match, every zone, and every elimination could decide a team’s fate. Which 8 will survive and BEAT THE HEAT?

🔥 Why You Can’t Miss 2025 PMWC at EWC:
- High-pressure matches for survival!
- 16 teams, only 8 tickets to the Grand Finals!
- Cheer for your favorite region and team as they chase the $3,000,000 and a crown!
- Exciting SMASH RULE format in Grand Finals! 

🔥 How does SMASH RULE work in Grand Finals? 
After Day 2 of Grand Finals, the Match Point Threshold will be set to the #1 ranked team’s points +10. Any team that hits this must then win a later match to claim the trophy in the last day of Grand Finals—winning the same match where they reach the threshold doesn’t bring the championship. If no team secures the title via SMASH Rule by Match 18, the team with the highest total points wins under standard rules.
